          "tz": -300
        },
        "subject": "LU-9964 ldlm: Prevent multiple group locks",
        "message": "LU-9964 ldlm: Prevent multiple group locks\n\nThere are two ways in which we can get multiple group locks\non the same resource (which is invalid because it breaks\nvarious requirements for page writeback):\n\n1. Multiple requests can go to the server at the same time\nand the server will grant them (as they are compatible)\nSolution: Wait in OSC layer for compatible group lock\nrequests to be granted\n2. When being destroyed, group locks must eventually stop\nmatching new i/o so they can complete writeout and\ndestruction.  When this happens (by setting cbpending in\nldlm_cli_cancel_local), another request can be sent to the\nserver and be granted before the lock finishes writing out\ndirty pages.\nSolution: Wait (in ldlm_lock_match) for any group locks\nwith no references to be done (LDLM_FL_BL_DONE), so\ncancellation is complete and only freeing remains to do.\nAt this point, pages are written out and the lock is no\nlonger associated with a resource.  This makes it safe to\nrequest a new lock.\n\nMore details about this (including why it can't be solved\nserver side) are in LU-9964.\n\nSigned-off-by: Patrick Farrell <paf@cray.com>\nChange-Id: Ia3c86b605cbc6360529e5cd07b960874c54921a2\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
